#Thunderstaff (#1085), prevention leg - PARKED, engine-blocked. Oracle: while
#untapped, if a creature would deal combat damage to me, prevent 1 (giant
#should deal 2 -> life 18; master deals the full 3).
#MAPPED: the script grants "absorb:<count of attackers>" to the CONTROLLER (a
#player). ABSORB only works on card targets (Damage.cpp:101 reduces damage
#when the target has it); the basicAbility enum's own comment says absorb
#"need[s] to be coded for players too" - player-side absorb is unimplemented,
#so the grant silently does nothing. Engine fuel: implement player ABSORB in
#Damage.cpp (and ensure the grant machinery can set basicAbilities on a
#player), then enable this test. Thunderstaff is the only absorb: user.
[INIT]
firstmain
[PLAYER1]
inplay:thunderstaff
[PLAYER2]
inplay:hill giant
library:darksteel citadel,millstone
[DO]
goto end
goto attackers
hill giant
next
next
goto secondmain
[ASSERT]
SECONDMAIN
[PLAYER1]
life:18
inplay:thunderstaff
[PLAYER2]
inplay:hill giant
hand:*
library:darksteel citadel
[END]
